Lodewijk Frans Asscher (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈloːdəˌʋɛi̯k frɑns ˈɑʃər]; born 27 September 1974) is a Dutch politician of the Labour Party (PvdA). He served as Deputy Prime Minister of the Netherlands and Minister of Social Affairs and Employment in the Second Rutte cabinet from 5 November 2012 to 26 October 2017. He previously was appointed as Acting Mayor of Amsterdam from 12 March 2010 to 7 July 2010 after Job Cohen resigned to become the Labour Party leader for the Dutch general election of 2010.
